AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2293* House Bill No. 2359
by inserting the following new sections immediately preceding the last section and renumbering
the subsequent section accordingly:
SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 67-4-1035(e), is amended by
deleting the subsection and substituting instead:
(e) The alcoholic beverage commission and local law enforcement agencies
have concurrent jurisdiction with the department of revenue to enforce violations of title
39, chapter 17, part 15. The commission and local law enforcement agencies may
investigate such violations, conduct unannounced compliance checks, and arrest
individuals based on probable cause of noncompliance.
SECTION 5. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 67-4-1035, is amended by adding
the following new subsection:
( ) The commission shall hire a sufficient number of employees, as determined
by the commission, to enforce this section. The commission shall establish the salaries
of the employees hired under this section, and such employees serve at the pleasure of
the commission.
